title: Bug 4121 - JarExporter causes out of Sync
description: When exporting a directory (project) and placing the exported jar in the same directory (project), overwriting the exported jar file for the second time results in an out of sync message.
OB: When exporting a directory (project) and placing the exported jar in the same directory (project), there is no warning or error message indicating that this could cause an issue.
EB: The exported jar file should include a warning or error message when attempting to overwrite itself in the same directory (project).
SR: Provide a warning or error message when attempting to overwrite the exported jar file in the same directory (project), indicating that this action may cause synchronization issues.
